title: For Sale:  Armalite AR-7 Israeli Military 22lr
postcontent:
Pix #1 In the late 1960's Israel ordered an unknown quantity of Armalite AR-7 22lr cal semi auto survival rifles. They made the various modifications pictured here, provided a canvas roll bag. The set was then strapped to the ejection seat in their fighter aircraft. A few years ago less than 200 of them were imported into the U.S.

Pix #2, Among the Israeli modifications was to shorten the barrel to 13 inches. Before the importer could re-sell the guns he had to attach the 3 inch simulated muzzle break to bring it back out to a legal minimum 16".

Pix #3, Nearly all the changes made to the gun were done with pre-existing parts. Note the grip is for an FAL. Forward sling swivel is for an L1A1. I'm not sure what the canvas sling was used on but it is original to the gun.

Pix #4, Close up of the barrel just ahead of the chamber. Note the serial numbered on the barrel not done on factory Armalites. Also the importer's stamp under  The Armalite address.(not shown)

Pix #5, Barrel removed & stock collapsed. Package length would have been 13" had the 3" barrel extension not been added for legality. Note the front sight, it's for a K98 Mauser!(not shown)

Liquidating my 30 year private collection. Everything I don't actually use must go. Would consider a partial trade for Stainless Marlin Papoose, or TC barrels in 30 carb & 45 acp.

Local sale to legally authorized individual, or will ship to FFL dealer.

title: For Sale:  Remington 591M  5mm magnum (Craig)  ##SOLD##
location: Cary, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
Something unusual and a ton of fun.  I have taken squirrels out past 150 yds with no exaggeration.  The rifle is in excellent condition with a few minor "vault dings" and the blueing is rich and 95% or better.  These rifles were made from 1970-74 but were before thier time.  The ammo was expensive and the round never "caught on".  The round shoots as flat as the .17 and hits harder than the 22mag.  I got the rifle, had it converted to centerfire (Craig Conversion), purchased a custom set of RCBS dies, virgin brass, and molly bullets.

Remington 591M 5mm Mag converted to centerfire (Craig conversion).  This rifle was manufactured in 1973.  Like I previously stated the condition is remarketable for 40 years old!  Included is approx 100 rnds of brass, about 100 bullets, 1lb of Win 296, custon RCBS dies w/ extended shell holder, Bushnell 3x9 40mm banner scope , rings, and mounts.

I have over $1100.00 invested and am only getting rid of her due to an injury that precludes my ability to hunt.  If you want something that is different and a blast to shoot please take a look.  The Craig round: 36gr @ 2300+fps, the rifle has excellent accuracy and a crisp trigger.  The weal part of these rifles is the mgazine, the magazine is in excellent shape condition.  The .204 bullet is now widely available and you can get bullet weights to 50grs.  I have better pics and will provide upon request.

Thanks for your time.
